description:
Zebar creates cross-platform taskbars, desktop widgets, and popups.

Zebar is a tool for creating customizable and cross-platform taskbars, desktop widgets, and popups.
🎉 New features
- Add errors.log file for error dumps.
- Add configurable stdout logging verbosity with new --quiet and --verbose CLI flags.
- Allow fractional units for widget width, length, and offset (e.g. 90.5%).
- Add tauriWindow getter and close function to currentWidget.
// ## For example, auto-close a widget when focus is lost (e.g. for popups like calendars, volume).
// ## Best used with "Focus on launch" option enabled for widgets.

// Listen to widget losing focus.
zebar.currentWidget().tauriWindow.listen("tauri://blur", () => {
  zebar.currentWidget().close(); // close the widget!
});


🐛 Bug fixes
- Prevent memory buildup from debug logging (#226).
- Fix widget z-order not working (always on top/bottom).
- Add better handling for apps that emit frequent systray update events.
- Fix 404 error when installing Zebar with an instance already running.
- Fix "Empty cache & reload configs" menu option not relaunching widget windows.
- Fix "Run on startup-up" menu option not working in some scenarios.
⚠️ Deprecations
// Previously:
const tauriWindow = currentWidget().window.tauri; 

// After:
const tauriWindow = currentWidget().tauriWindow;


/ @lars-berger
